The President also announced ministers, their deputies and premiers will donate a third of their salaries to the COVID-19 Solidarity Fund. And they will do so for the next three months. Cyril Ramaphosa is calling on business executives to follow their lead. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa and his Cabinet will take pay cuts. He also encouraged executives of large companies to make a similar gesture. READ: Lockdown extended by two weeks Ramaphosa has announced that the national lockdown has been extended by a further two weeks. South Africa had been placed on a 21-day lockdown by the president in a bid to curb the spread of the coronavirus. The lockdown had been due to end on 16 April. There are currently 1,934 COVID-19 confirmed cases in South Africa with 18 fatalities.